f%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Meng%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20working%20on%20the%20project%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20active%20probing%20involves%20sending%20a%20%26quot%3Bping%26quot%3B%20to%20Gaza%20and%20expecting%20to%20receive%20a%20%26quot%3Bpong%26quot%3B%20from%20Palestinian%20routers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20less%20than%2020%25%20of%20networks%20in%20Gaza%20are%20responding%20to%20these%20probes%2C%20a%20stark%20drop%20from%20the%20previous%2090%25%20before%20the%20conflict%20began%2C%20the%20project%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECellular%20data%20is%20down%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20follow-up%20email%2C%20Meng%20said%20that%20their%20data%20most%20likely%20reflects%20a%20decline%20in%20fixed-line%20internet%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20access%20to%20the%20typically%20slow%20and%20insecure%202G%20cellular%20data%2C%20which%20Gaza%20is%20reliant%20on%2C%20also%20appears%20to%20be%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20strikes%20have%20damaged%20buildings%20containing%20telecommunications%20installations%2C%20destroying%20two%20of%20the%20three%20lines%20for%20mobile%20communications%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fcontent%2Fhostilities-gaza-strip-and-israel-flash-update-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20Office%20for%20the%20Coordination%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20(OCHA).%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOCHA%20said%20the%20strikes%20have%20left%20just%20one%20line%20working%20%E2%80%94%20Paltel%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Telecommunications%20Company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20line%20also%20appears%20to%20have%20disrupted%20service%2C%20with%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPaltelco%2Fstatus%2F1711701294270865465%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Paltel%20warning%20last%20week%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20any%20more%20disruption%20to%20lines%20connecting%20Gaza%20to%20the%20outside%20world%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20total%