.com%2Fhow-interbreeding-between-humans-and-neanderthals-affects-our-health-today-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20sexual%20encounters%20mean%20Neanderthal%20genes%20have%20been%20passed%20down%20through%20the%20generations%2C%20and%20today%20most%20people%20can%20thank%20Neanderthals%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1004944%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThanks%2520to%2520genome%2520sequencing%2520and%2Corigin%2520in%2520present%252Dday%2520Eurasians.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%202%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20genomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neanderthal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e4e9fff0438955586558f24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222342%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20employee%20of%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20in%20London%20looks%20at%20model%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20male%2F%3Cp%3EWill%20Oliver%2FPA%20Images%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20proportion%20varies%2C%20and%20some%20people%20have%20slightly%20more%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20than%20others.%20People%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Fneanderthal-dna-you-carry-may-have-surprisingly-little-impact-your-looks-moods%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEast%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20notably%2C%20tend%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-genes-lower-risk-severe-coronavirus-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20Neanderthal%20DNA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20genomes%2C%20but%20why%20they%20have%20more%20has%20long%20baffled%20scientists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Neanderthals%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20mostly%20been%20European.%20Some%20Neanderthal%20remains%20were%20found%20as%20far%20East%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-humans-interbreed-with-mysterious-population-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAltai%20Mountains%20of%20Siberia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20their%20bones%20are%20usually%20found%20in%20European%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20logical%20conclusion%20would%20be%20that%20the%20first%20children%20of%20Homo%20Sapiens%20and%20Neanderthals%20would%20have%20been%20born%20in%20Europe.%20The%20next%20logical%20step%20is%20that%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20would%20get%20more%20diluted%20as%20Homo%20sapiens%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhuman-genome-overlaps-neanderthals-ancestors-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emingled%20with%20other%20humans%20and%20hominins%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they%20spread%20away%20from%20the%20area%20where%20Neanderthals%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20what's%20puzzling%20is%20that%20an%20area%20where%20we've%20never%20found%20any%20Neanderthal%20remains%2C%20there's%20more%20Neanderthal%20DNA%2C%26quot%3B%20study%20author%20Mathias%20Currat%2C%20a%20geneticist%C2%A0at%20the%20University%20of%20Geneva%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F18%2Fworld%2Fneanderthal-ancestry-dna-percentage-scn%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.adg9817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%20Advances%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wednesday%2C%20may%20provide%20some%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrat%20and%20his%20co-authors%20drew%20from%20a%20database%20of%204%2C000%20human%20genomes%20extracted%20from%20human%20remains%20dating%20back%20up%20to%2040%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20held%20by%20the%20Harvard%20Medical%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20study%20found%20that%20up%20to%20about%2020%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20European%20genomes%20were%20indeed%20richer%20in%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20than%20the%20Asian%20genomes%20they%20have%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20proportion%20shifted%20about%205%2C000%20to%2010%2C000%20years%20ago.%20What%20the%20scientists%20think%20happened%20then%20is%20that%20a%20group%20of%20farming%20Homo%20sapiens%20from%20Anatolia%2C%20now%20Western%20Turkey%2C%20started%20mixing%20with%20hunter-gatherers%20in%20Western%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20farmers%20had%20a%20little%20less%20Neanderthal%20in%20them%2C%20so%20Western%20Europeans%20lost%20some%20of%20that%20ancestry%20as%20they%20mixed%2C%20Currat%20said%2C%20per%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20not%20quite%20clear%2C%20however%2C%20is%20what%20happened%20in%20Asia.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%20the%20database%20the%20scientists%20were%20looking%20at%20had%20a%20lot%20less%20information%20about%20Asian%20genomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20that%20archaeological%20excavations%20have%20been%20much%20more%20numerous%20in%20Europe%2C%20which%20greatly%20facilitates%20the%20study%20of%20the%20genomes%20of%20European%20populations%2C''%20said%20study%20author%20Claudio%20Quilodr%C3%A1n%2C%20a%20geneticist%20at%20the%20UNIGE%20Faculty%20of%20Science%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1004944%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThanks%2520to%2520genome%2520sequencing%2520and%2Corigin%2520in%2520present%252Dday%2520Eurasians.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20accompanying%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-more-neanderthal-dna-others-scientists-why-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697716079000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6531166396f7540cd060363d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-more-neanderthal-dna-others-scientists-why-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20ha